caption: I'm a First time customer! On my way home to try their food. But smells good and nice staff.
Amazing local BBQ place with a well known reputation in the neighborhood.
The food is delicious 😋 , I was hoping that I could sit in but not yet

A bbq joint that you can always count on to serve up fresh and tasty food! My wife is a vegetarian and is very picky about veggie burgers, but the one they serve is her favorite! They have excellent food for carnivores and herbivores.
Quality of food has gone downhill. Mac n cheese is just sad now. This used to be a favorite spot to order from. No more.
Food is delicious service is excellent greens & corn bread is my favorite.

We're from the South and this place if some of the best BBQ I've had outside of the South.  I"ve eaten at the hole-in-the-wall places and the big chains in Tennessee, Alabama, and Texas and Wrigley is right in the mix with them!
bbq and the atmosphere at this spot is great. Food was so delicious. The staff was friendly and sociable. The bill won't shock you. This place has many great reviews for a reason.
This place is delicious.  Get the 3/4 meat combo and load up.  They have quite a few nice sauces, try them all and get extra!  Awesome sides.  Friendly service.  Recommended and will return.
Genuine BBQ! Been going for several years and never been disappointed. Love the crew there!

Had a real hankering for ribs. Ordered the full slab -- and boy, did they satisfy! Well done (which I love), seasoned just right with sauces that complemented perfectly (I like the Memphis Sweet, husband likes the Texas habanero). Extremely high quality. Love the coleslaw, too -- the vinegar kind, but not too sharp.

This place is fantastic. I got the pulled pork plate and there is SO much pork. Not even a touch dry and the Memphis bbq sauce that came with it is amazing as well. Not to mention a super friendly staff. Do them a favor and order directly from their website and make the walk over. You and them both save a couple bucks!

Ordered the pulled pork and some brisket sliders, and was not disappointed.  Sides were excellent and the staff and cooks in the open kitchen are friendly and funny.  Great atmosphere.  Let's keep this place open because I can't wait to see how much fun the place would be packed with people after the pandemic.  Support small businesses!

A top site for delicious BBQ. One of the best spots in the area. Looking forward to coming back with my relatives. The prices are well within reason for the quality. Makes me feel like I am back in Sacramento.
Food is amazing!!! Love the wrigley fire sauce!!!
Good place for bbq. Certainly worth a return trip.
Amazing value. I go at least once a month

Such good food! A great place to pick up food and walk over to the lake for a picnic. Also looks like dine-in will be fun, once Covid ends. *Note, I was hungry and I can pack away a good amount, but I had two slices of Brisket AND half the mashed sweet potato left for tomorrow. They definitely get five stars for portions! 10/10 will be back!
Good enough ribs. Coleslaw and fried pickles were a bit bland. Found a big hair in the coleslaw
One of my preferred places for tasty bbq. I love it here. Quick, helpful, and friendly service. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.
A preferred place for BBQ. Service is always nice even when they have a full house. I will be back with my relatives. Bring your appetite because portions are large.
My preferred spot for BBQ. Great place to chill, get away, eat some good food. It has a nice atmosphere. This place has good reviews for a reason.
Just look at this. A pool of grease at the bottom where it the chicken was sitting, chicken not even half breaded, and to top it all off, not even remotely hot. Couldn't even eat it.
Omg best bbq place eva. Luv lots.
Just the right spicy, great BBQ flavor love it .

I love the flavors of the barbecue here! The meat is cooked just right and juicy, and the sauces are so flavorful with a hint of spice. The portion size on the nachos is great, big enough for 2 meals.

Anyone who says the bbq here is good has NEVER had actual bbq. The brisket had NO flavor, was super bland and incredibly touch. It’s supposed to be JUICY. The ribs, my god, the ribs shouldn’t even exist. Their ribs were BURNT and stuck together with no flavor, had to use a pair of pliers to pull them apart. Ribs are supposed to fall off the bones easily. Everything tasted like gas and like the metal grill. They are not smoking their meat properly at all. You’re better off walking a few extra steps to the jewel next door and getting whatever frozen bbq they have their, cheaper AND better tasting. Can’t believe this place has the audacity to call whatever it serves as BBQ. DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY HERE.  -An extremely disappointed Texan living in Chicago
This place is a must if you’re looking for good bbq in Chicago! The staff is some of the best in the city and quality is never in question here. Take the time to check these guys out!
This is the worst BBQ i ever had.  the rid tips are dry and the bbq chicken is from the oven . I would not recommend this place to anyone.

Just tried this place for the first time since moving here in AUGUST (my mistake)... and the chopped beef sandwich was great. Sauces are a little pickley tasting but still good. The best sweet potato fries I’ve ever had (not an exaggeration).

Picked up a meal during the shutdown and everything was perfect. The meats were smoked to tenderness with the right amount of seasoning, even the sides stand on their own which is where a lot of BBQ places fall short.  Staff were friendly and packaged everything well for travel.
Delicious brisket. Wrigley Fire sauce is the right amount of spice.
One of my preferred places to grab some food. excellent location, neat, and great service. I recommend this place!
Great food and great service!
Great service, great food, great atmosphere, and great prices 👍🏼
Very well organised and welcoming place. They offer large portions and for economical prices. We liked the meals very much and the staff members were very affable and explanatory. Recommended.
My favorite BBQ place in Chicago!
Love this place. They are always so nice and the food is my favorite Chinese take out in Salt Lake. I love the Lo Mein!
Had a fantastic experience in this place with my daughter. The food came quick and the customer service is just fantastic. Prices are convenient.

I go to this unique place once a month because I like the good air that is unique to this place. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably helpful and skilfull. The service is awfully rapid. Also, the food you eat is outstanding. I have been there more than once and I was always satisfied. The rate is honest. I highly recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.
The food is consistently well prepared and tasty, workers hands out excellent service. I really like the cleanliness and character. Will visit here again.
Yumm
Exceptional place to have food when in a rush. Their customer service is speedy, prices are fair, great vibes. Will come visit again
This spot gives amazing service and delicious menu. The best place around town. The food and drinks came out fast and the prices are fair. I recommend this place.
This spot clearly knows how to serve their customers. Regularly with a very friendly attitude. The food is fairly priced, regularly yummy and neat.

I came in on the weekend with a large group of friends and we were seated and had our food quick. The service was super friendly and nice. The food was absolutely delicious. This is my first time and I’ll be back!
Nothing special,you find what you looking for but thats it.Mediocre.
Love this place, they have the best brisket in Chicago. They give generous portions and the workers are quite friendly

The ribs were fantastic! Huge servings and the staff were friendly. There's also 5 different sauces to choose from which they bring straight to your table. It's a great spot to check out whenever you're craving for some BBQ.

I celebrated my nomination yesterday in this gorgeous place. happy to tell that we had a marvelous evening and the venue was certainly the reason for that strong celebration. The team  contributed in a very nice style, the food was yummy and my guests were so  overjoyed. We shall absolutely visit again for more joyful events. Thank you very much.
Good portions and sauce options.
Food was great and service was quick!
Waooo, the food is very good, the meat is super soft and juicy, the fries god of wonder and the salad a success.
Amazing food with big proportions!
Everything’s so great!!!!

Tried both the brisket and pork; both were tender and delicious.  Portion sizes were VERY generous.  Texas sauce was spicy, and Memphis sauce was sweet.  Both were good.  Combining them was best.  Good value for the money.

Im from Texas!!!  Baked Beans = FIRE!! The BEST beans I have ever had in my entire LIFE!! Amazing taste, flavor, and mixture of different kinds of beans!! 5 stars!!!  Baby back ribs = awkward flavor of seasoning, but of good quality, so I give them 4 stars. The TX Habenero BBQ sauce was gross!  Smoked Turkey = Dry, dry, dry, dry...flavorless, flavorless, flavorless....The End...2 stars only because they actually use real turkey breast, which is really part of the problem. They under seasoned it and overcooked.  Mac & cheese = or should I say "Death by Mac and cheese"! Negative 7 stars!! I don't know who gave them the recipe for their Mac and cheese or if they stole it out of Martha Stewart's cookbook, but it's TRASH! I put salt on it and had to mix it with the beans in order to eat it. They seriously should look for some different recipes on the internet and just try them out. Maybe have a Mac and cheese taste test with the locals or something.
I didn't like the bar b que.
Has potential.. the brisket was really good.. I also enjoyed the baked beans .m
Realy good BBQ
They don't skimp on the serving size and the bbq is exceptional. Great prices.
Great food, Wrigley Fire sauce is amazing, and they have Cheerwine on tap!!
Best BBQ in town for sure.

Brisket and pulled pork were excellent. Beans and mac and cheese were good. They provide 4 different BBQ sauces and all were great.Two meat tray with two sides should be enough for two people and is only priced around 18 dollars. Clean bathroom as well. Definitely one of my better Chicago meals and will likely visit again.
Visiting for work and can say this is the best bbq I have ever had. Had the brisket with mac and cheese and corn bread. You won't be disapointed!!

I loved the food, you order and prepay and somebody brings you the food to your table, there is no waiter serving you water, I wish they had the choice to tip 10% instead of 15% which I thought it was too much for a cafeteria style service. Still recommend this place because the food is really good
Good was great
Best BBQ in Chicago. Hands down. This has become my go-to place to eat out at! Best variety of unique sauces. Incredibly friendly staff, too.
Really enjoyed our dinner here tonight.  Beef and pork were very tasty. Other two in our party had the specials which were very good.  Staff was super nice and helpful.
I know this place might be considered  heavier food but i tried a few brisket and smoked meat places in west loop but this tops them all.. super good... It is a spot to try for sure..
Solid bbq in lake shore east. They can sometimes do burnt ends if you ask nicely
Food was really good!! Turkey was a little dry.
A great discovery, the ribs and sides were delicious, the people very friendly. I've already started to share WBBQ with friends.
Good food, friendly service
excellent smoked ribs, Maybe the best. Often with deal specials that make it even better. The slaw and corn bread are also worth the time and money
Always great food
The food was just alright. The brisket was dry and bland, but the sweet potato fries were decent and the corn bread was delicious.
How does a pulled pork sandwich take over 30 min to make? It wasn't even that busy
The ribs are "dry" so never over sauced. Selection of delicious sauces.

I had the chicken platter, with green beans and sweet potato fries! Even though the chicken was a bit dry, but I enjoyed the meal, large portion, friendly staff, great atmosphere. Absolutely loved the sauces! I will definitely return to try their ribs!
My order of ribs were burnt til inedible.  If I didnt live so far ai definitely would have taken them back.
Just moved to Chicago and love the BBQ here and this place was great

This place has a nice atmosphere, friendly staff and excellent food. Its situated close to Wrigley field on the Northern edge of Boystown, it's in a fantastic area.  I brought my parents here when they came to visit and they wanted to go back again the following night. Can't recommend it highly enough.
Love their food and service.
This place is tasty. The people are nice and the Memphis Sweet sauce is deeelicious. If I want bbq and I don't feel like firing up my own grill this is definitely a top contender.
Try the black bean burger...excellent! They'll give you  your choice of bbq sauce too! The sides are amazing, especially the coleslaw!

The food was pretty good! The people were very nice as well. I had the ribs, brisket and pulled pork...The ribs were the best. Brisket was a bit dry. The sauce options were great and plentiful. Its a bit expensive but i wouldnt mind trying something different from their menu again.
Pretty decent
Fast, great customer service, and amazing food. We will definitely be returning!
Delicious as always.
The Service was great and so was the food
All Bar-Be-Cue Is Awesome !

Had the brisket platter, huge serving size. Unfortunately they have those long fried pickles but they aren't too big thankfully. The brisket was recommended but wasn't amazing but the slaw was really good and went well with the brisket. All of the sauces there are really mild in flavor and spice which could be improved.
Delicious food. I had the pulled pork sandwich and it was the best!
The pulled pork here is phenomenal. I also didn't know that dipping fried pickles in ranch was a thing.  It is.  You should try it.  I recommend this place to as many people as I can.
Deliciousness!
It’s consistently good every time. You won’t be disappointed. The wrigley fire sauce is some of the better hot bbq I’ve had.
Excellent Q & Service
First time at this restaurant but won’t be the last.  Food was good and the service was excellent!
Love this place for a quick bite. Their sauce selection is bomb and their portion sizes are ideal. I always leave feeling filled.
Some of the best BBQ on the north side of Chicago with good prices. Staff is attentive. Also have non-meat options.
Great Food!
Great BBQ....the side order food isn't always fresh, leftover from the day before

We've eaten here several times but can't remember the food being this quality. Today we tried the wings, ribs, and brisket and all were overly dry. The brisket was exceptionally dry. It's surprising that a bbq joint came up short on all 3.
The ribs might as well have been made of rubber. Absolute trash.
Twas a good standard. Want a lot of good food? Go here, easy.
Great food + friendly staff! The brisket is delicious.

Fast and easy. While we were waiting on our food an employee came to ask if there was a particular sports game we would like to have on the TV(we were the only people inside). I thought that was a great gesture

Great food and even greater portions, at a REALLY reasonable price. The atmosphere was very laid back and comfortable. We were taken care of by the staff and plan to return again with friends. Such a great place and easy to get to. Comfort food at it's best! Carolina Vinegar sauce was my #1
So happy I tried this local spot. Delicious, perfectly friend pork sandwich (will have to go back for the actual BBQ)! The service was very kind and attentive as well.
Super hot guy working register lol gave him 5 bucks CALL ME XOXOXO
Great briskets! Love going there
Friendly spot, awesome rib tips.
Awesome BBQ and great staff. Best fried pickles!
All of it amazing! Very small - no where to sit. We always go eat it on the beach recommend everything!!!

I've had pretty much everything from here over the last few years, and I always leave happy. Arrive early enough if you want to pick from your choice of meat; they run out of most things toward closing time.
Former Texan- unfortunately the meat was over cooked but the sides, mash potatoes and cornbread were good. The people working there were great.

Love this place!  I first found out about them when we booked them to cater our small wedding rehearsal dinner.  They actually never ended up receiving the order due to someone (who apparently no longer works there) never entered it.  So when I called the day of the rehearsal wondering where our food was, the owner answered and personally prepared and delivered our entire order immediately.  He even gave us a generous credit for his restaurant.  Given the sincere attempt to make up for the situation, and the quality of the food, Wrigley BBQ has become our go to BBQ spot.  The people there are always great.  I've gotten the ribs every time and my wife loves the pulled pork (there's always enough to take home leftovers).  And I highly recommend any of their desserts!
Really good veggie burger, sides were awesome. Will come again.
Good food and reasonable prices. Try the sweet potato fries.

I've ate a few meals at Wrigley BBQ and have to say they are sub par for a BBQ joint. The only thing I would consider they do well is fried pickles. The brisket was dry, their pulled pork was below average, and the Mac n Cheese is synonymous with what you'd get from a frozen dinner. You can try to drown in on their mediocre sauces that are what you'd expect from even the most basic BBQ place. If in the area I'd say save your money and go somewhere else.
Great smoked meat, great burgers, great sauces, and great people. Highly recommended.
The brisket was not smoked, but rather boiled, a real disappointment. Also, very lean meat, not the typical brisket style. Friendly staff doesn’t help if the food is just not what it should be.
Online menu different from store menu need to update
Good BBQ, cool little shop for after the game.

They basically ran out of half of the menu and their Infamous deep dish pizza took 30 minutes to prepare. And of course all the appetizers I wanted to tide me over until that pizza was ready, were out.

This is a great place for ribs, pulled pork, and brisket. Sometimes the sides were a bit stale, but the ribs are always great and the brisket is amazing. They also recently added beef ribs, which I tried, but I prefer the pork ribs better. They play sports games here, and the environment is fun!
The best pulled pork ever
The best place to have a bbq dinner. The taste is amazing and the amount of sides and meat is so big. I didn’t finish my meal. The service is super and friendly environment.
The brisket was tender and juicy however, everything lacked overall flavor. The Carolina mustard sauce was great.

I live two blocks from this place, so I'm a frequent customer here.  Love the food, everything I've tried is great.  I'm from Kansas City, so the sweet Memphis BBQ is my favorite (since it's closest to KC flavor)!
I absolutely love this place! Staff is super friendly and food is delicious. Best BBQ in Wrigleyville hands down!!!
Great food, next time if the brisket is tough, I'll ask for another meat.
Stopped in for lunch.  The service was outstanding.  I had the pork nachos they were fabulous. Will defintely stop by again.
The chicken was SO juicy, oh my God!
Great brisket sandwich, nice price.  Should be more people in there.

The service is superb.  The staff is extremely friendly and seem to be genuinely eager to ensure a great dining experience.  The food is cooked to perfection, and the portions are plentiful.  I highly recommend Wrigley BBQ!!!
Amazing pulled pork tacos, $10 for three.  Great place to get some food after a Cubbie game!
It was very clean and staff were very nice.

Excellent meals! We both got the 2 meat combo with different meats and sides and we  both loved our meals. There is no alcohol served here but you can  stop next door at Jewel/Osco, pick up your pleasure, and enjoy with your meal.  I highly recommend!!
Great short rib and corn bread. Good selection of BBQ sauces

This was fantastic barbeque for so far away from Kansas City. The brisket had great taste, and the BBQ sauce was a tasty addition. The ribs also had great taste, and the barbeque sauce made them perfect. I also had mac and cheese and tots. Everything about this meal was awesome, including the beer I bought next door and brought with me. I highly recommend.

Tried three different things and although food wasn’t to die for and I wouldn’t necessarily come back for it, I would come back for the A1 service and try something else. The older gentleman at the counter that took our order and brought our food out was the nicest man I’ve came into contact with in awhile. He really enjoyed his job and was very spunky. The food isn’t the only aspect that matters in a restaurant— the service is too!
Great customer service and BBQ.
Good spot for some BBQ
I really enjoyed the ribs. Sides are great. This place somehow has managed to capture the authentic feel of a Southern BBQ place.
Good food
Great food and service!
Clean,  great atmosphere, fair prices,  diverse menu. The way BBQ should be presented. Fond of Texas BBQ?  This establishment is right on course and brings you back home.

Yum yum yum. Went there with a friend for dinner. The service was great. You walk up and order order then sit  The pleasantly professional young lady that took our order made sure we know about the specials and explained the different sauces to us. We ordered a chicken sandwich with fries for$8 and a large order of rib tips that was on the specials of the day for $9. The food was brought out to us promptly by a very nice server who went above and beyond making sure we had all we needed. The staff is nice and professional, the prices are just right, the portions are generous and the food was great. This is going on my list of favorites.

Good pulled chicken sandwich and fries! Not many options for bbq sauce however the ones they have are not bad.  Friendly staff and fast service.  Great place to stop and cool off on a hot summer day for sure.   Gladly go again

AMAZING!!!!!! Great food, friendly staff . We came right when they just closed ,but the man in the back took our order anyway, and the food is definitely worth the 45 min drive from our house . We will be going back .
Great food at a great price for the area. Highly recommended. I will be going here every time I'm in the are. Way to knock it out of the park. Thanks Joel and the rest of the crew.
Two words, fried pickles and Cheerwine
amazing ribs!!!
There is a nice variety of choices on the menu. Not too crowded, and food was delicious!

Best wings around. Get them smoked for sure. Plenty of meat and they are the full bad boys, not the fake wannabe wings. Staff is great. Can swing next door to Joe's to grab a beer to wait for your food.
Tasty BBQ walking distance from wriggly field!
The southwest salad is amazing! It even comes with pieces of jalapeno cornbread on top.
Food was very delicious. Highly recommend their burgers for lunch.
For the north, excellent brisket and sauce. Good value.
Very high quality and great tasting BBQ at nice prices. I particularly love their brisket.
The brisket is amazing.
Best Rib's in neighborhood, Jack the owner knows food! +moderately priced, BYOB
Great BBQ. Decent sauces. Mac & cheese is fantastic. Also vegetarian friendly, with a black bean burgers and new Impossible Burger! BYOB.
Excellent.  Large portions.  Very friendly staff.
Great food great service
Good sauces and very yummy food. Probably the best BBQ in the area.

I live across the street from Wrigley Barbecue and just tried the Smoked Gouda cheeseburger with  mashed sweet potatoes and baked beans as side orders. Two days later, I ordered the turkey sandwich with fries.  The food is extremely high quality and excellent.  The restaurant has a relaxed, friendly atmosphere. I highly recommend!!
Best BBQ in Chicago hands down!

Absolutely love baby back ribs and brisket here. Honestly I would come back here and try some more of the menu that I didn’t try yet. I heard so many good thing about this place from his regular customer.

Awesome ribs and best service!!!  Went to eat there the other night, with my wife and I being new to the area, and we were blown away.  Besides being extremely courteous and friendly, their ribs are HUGE!  Unknowingly, we ordered two full racks and could only finish half of one between the both of us.  Even the cook came out to greet us and checked to see if everything tasted to our satisfaction.  They also have awesome chili, so highly recommend this place!
AMAZING. Pulled pork sandwich, brisket sandwich, mac n cheese, corn bread, southwest chopped salad, everything was fantastic. Employees were pleasant too. Definitely give it a try!
Best BBQ place in all of Chicago, probably. To be fair, technically the only one I've been to. But it's great and I love it.
Wrigley BBQ is a great neighborhood place with takeout or delivery. They have a selection of wonderful sauces and meats with which to construct your order.
Best BBQ in the neighborhood - if not in Chicago. We always stop by to grab a bite to eat. Definitely try the brisket and the pulled pork sandwich! Very quick service and they also deliver.
I love this place. The brisket is my favorite. The wings are ok.
Great BBQ place a few blocks away from Wrigley. BYOB for your own alcohol though.
Outstanding BBQ, and they deliver. They do classic sides like fried pickles and baked beans. You order at the counter, and they bring you deliciousness!
The BBQ and BRISKET Sandwiches are very tasty

Man I've never paid this much for BBQ. I couldn't afford to give this place more stars because I had to pawn them all off to pay for my meal. To make things worse, this BBQ was Dog Dookie. Might as well pick up a rotisserie around the corner at the Jewell-Osco.
Best barbeque in the city!
One of my favorite places for cheap greasy eats, especially fried pickles.

Live right by here and used to be good but our last visit was a huge let down. No one in the place and food still came out cold. The only warm portion was a bone dry brisket. Will not visit again and seems to be trending downwards

I lived in Nashville for several years before this and this place does it right! Easily the best BBQ I've had in Chicago. Anybody that says the employees are rude, unkind, etc. are certainly wrong. I've been here several times and always been welcomed as I come through the door. Also their sauces are amazing. The Texas Habenero is fantastic if you like a kick. Would recommend to any BBQ lover!
Great food. Great music as we sat in and ate. Friendly staff.
(Translated by Google) Favorite bbq in chicago  (Original) Favorote bbq in chicago

The restaurant had an offer on Groupon so I decided to try it for the fist time.  Just prior to paying for my carryout order, I was told that it was under new management and that the offer would probably not be honored.  The gentleman at the counter was very kind and apologetic.  He offered sides and beverages for compensation.  However, the worst part of the experience was the food.  The bbq chicken, a half chicken and wings were awful.  Hopefully they will improve!
This is my third or fourth time here.  I wouldn't come back if it wasn't good!

The brisket was absolutely fantastic, sides and the sauces were on the same page. Quick to get the food considering the quality, and the owner was super friendly and looked like he was doing what he loved. I don't often find myself in chicago, but this will be on my list every time! If you want some amazing bbq, this is your place!
Love the bacon cheeseburger . Great service and quick and yummy food . You just cant go wrong !
Great service and food but way too expensive for a sandwich and small bowl of chili for 20$..received no sides with the sandwich.
Good half chicken, lots of options for sides.
Pretty good BBQ for the money. Several types of sauces, good meat selection as far as the old stapes. Pulled pork is a masterpiece but the ribs have come out a little burned a couple times.

This is one of my fave burger joints in Chicago, and the service is great. They are always so nice and friendly. Only sorda downside is that they're somewhat slow, so you'll wait a little (normal time, I guess, if you're with company,  otherwise it feels long, hahaha). You can order on their app and pick-up or have delivered, which is nice.
Their barbeque is decent, but not outstanding. Prices are low.
Delicious!!   I do pickup on WINGS!!!
Good food, great location near Wrigley Field.
Really good barbecue.  Not the BEST (hence the 4 stars) but definitely consistently very good.
Pulled pork had good flavor but the brisket was a little plain. I'd definitely go back though.
Pretty good barbecue for a small operation. Very solid burger.
Decent ribs.
Really good brisket!

The food is DELICIOUS! The bbq I'd give 10 stars if I could, but only once did I get a decent person at the counter. The other few times it's been some nasty attitude a**hole who can't admit that their equipment doesn't work and I've been treated like a criminal just trying to place an order. I've been denied service because they can't see to it that their card reader and/or Internet connection works and I get accused of being a bum when my card works just fine at any other store, restaurant or ATM!! Only THIS PLACE seems to have an issue with my card and as a person with a computer degree and a very good grasp of technology, I can assure them that they need to make sure their equipment works and that their telecommunications lines are in working order before you make a scene and accuse hard working people of being bums and trash!!!! I can always get cash at an ATM first, but I hate being treated like some POS that doesn't deserve anything.
Great sides and great BBQ! The only place I know that carries barqs red cream soda on tap!
😀 wowwww the best lunch I ate . Was fresh and taste so good
Bland and pricy but it will fill you up in a pinch
Delicious BBQ. I like that the BBQ sauce is do it yourself so you don't get an overload of sauce. Cornbread is phenomenal too.
I did not enjoy my food at all. Needless to say I wont be going back
Great food and a great atmosphere. The BBQ was incredable, next time im in the area im certainly coming back here again.
Garbage  &  cockroaches

This BBQ joint has good food. Sandwiches are sold ala carte with many sides to add. They also have dinner platters. I had the pulled pork sandwich which was very good. They have several sauces you can add yourself which I like to do. Seating could be a bit more comfortable. The staff was very friendly. TIP: review the paper menu on the counter it has more items then just the overhead board.
High quality food, good service, OK prices for the area.

Best BBQ I've had in Chicago. The prices are great - especially during the lunch hour. A variety of sauces for every taste. Mild for BBQ lovers and Fire for those that like to kick it up. BYOB - always a great addition to good food.

The food here is good but expensive. As a small, carry-out place I would love to be able to swing by here more often for dinner but I just can't afford it.  Also make sure you call ahead of time if you're in a hurry because it can take a while to get your food.

Best bar-b-q in the world! I'm from Memphis so i know good from good and this place is simply amazing. The guy that have the place 1 star because the server put a hot plate in front of a 10 month old should be asked why their 10 month old is eating bar-b-q. Anyway, try the pulled chicken sandwich and fried pickles, your mouth will thank you.

Came here with my friend my daughter and my 10 month old grandchild. Ordered food. It was over cooked. Then the waitress came back and set a HOT plate in front of the baby. Really? She was very rude and didn't seem to care. I will never come back and will never recommend this place!
Food is good, and it's BYOB!
They work hard to please the customer (which I appreciate), but they have let me down sometimes (no big deal though). I go only because it is convenient and a good quantitiy.
the memphis sweet wings are the best wings i've ever had. amazing bbq place. i've only lived in chicago for 3 months and I've had wrigley bbq at least 10 times.
Close by, very clean, nice staff and a small menu..but great food! Thanks guys :)
Fantastic!

I do not know much about BBW but this place was to die for. Everything my boyfriend and I ordered was out of this world. Their pulled pork was insanely flavorful. Also, their cornbread will knock your socks off. I miss living around the corner to this place.
This is a good new addition to the neighborhood. The food is good and takeout is quick and easy.

Are you lost? Just follow the smell of sweet smokey deliciousness like a Hansel and Gretel bread crumb path and you will find your way!  I always think twice before going to a three star rated restaurant, but that shouldn't sway you from checking out Wrigley BBQ if you live in the hood.  Order at the counter and they bring it to you, BYOB, only about 15 tables and yes the old Q-uizno's chairs from other reviews are funny!  Really enjoyed the pulled pork platter $11, tender and saucy, served with one piece of white bread. Mac and Cheese side is garlicy and amazing. Whipped maple sweet potatoes were good but I was bored after two bites. Jalapeno cornbread was a little dry, coleslaw was more basic than Jewel and really soupy.  Roommate said she makes better ribs, half rack $12, they had great color, lots of meat and little fat but she didn't think they were 'fallin off the bone' enough and actually left a few bites.
So good!  Friendly knowledgeable staff and REAL food!  So glad I stumbled upon this place

I waited until the third time I visited to write a review. Honestly, I don't know why I've been here three times - this is the worst BBQ I've had in Chicago.  The ribs come out cold every time, the burgers are bland, and the brisket is mediocre at best. The french fries are not seasoned and the cole slaw is essentially a soup.  As for the decor, I hope you enjoy chairs purchased from a Quiznos fire sale, because that's what you'll find here. To top it off, they are regularly out of drinks, ketchup, or sauces.  For the life of me, I cannot understand how this place has over four stars. The only explanation is that anyone who likes this place has literally never been to another BBQ restaurant.  If you enjoy food, I implore you, do not waste your time with Wrigleyville BBQ.

Woohoo! They open 11:30am everyday now! I can have it lunch or/and dinner any day I want! Yeah! Killer ribs, baked bean & mashed sweet potato, and corn bread, and... The bread pudding, and choco pecan bar are to die for!!! And my veggie friends love their veggie sandwich and salad. This place makes everyone HAPPY! :-)
Absolutely fantastic ribs.  By far the best BBQ in Chicago.

3 meat combo was great. BBQ shredded chicken, pulled pork & sliced brisket. I liked the chicken the best, great for sandwiches. Brisket was really well done, nice and tender. Sides were beans and coleslaw, neither of which were outstanding, but both good. Will definitely order again, and recommend to others looking for BBQ in the Lincoln Park/Lakeview neighborhoods.

Absolutely love this place. I always order the chopped brisket platter with corn and mac n cheese. The Texas Habanero BBQ sauce is my favorite. AND on top of this place's yummy goodness it's BYOB!! How could you go wrong? A+

I went there last year right after Opening Day, the place is only a 10 minute walk from Wrigley Field and the place was empty an hour after the sold out game......NOT a good sign....We were the only 2 people there. The BBQ was served cold, like it had been sitting around for awhile under a heat lamp and was tough and chewy. The portions were small considering the price.  I am a Chef and Pitmaster, I have worked in the Restaurant industry for over 25 years so yeah, I can tell good from bad, and this place was bad.  NOT recommended!!!
Great BBQ, reasonable prices, and close to home! Will definitely be a visiting again.
I've been here a few times. The food is pretty delicious and moderately priced. The staff is usually pretty friendly as well. If you're looking for BBQ food this is the place to go in East Lakeview.
the food was so good and at a really good price. the staff at wrigley are so friendly and helpful was such a good atmosphere.
Ive had super food in this restaurant numerous times and the prices are pretty reasonable too!! I would recommend the chicken wings cooked in memphis sweet!!! Definetely a must visit!!

Wrigley BBQ is an excellent local place to get good BBQ.  They have fair prices and friendly employees.  Lots of choices for sauces and different types of BBQ like ribs, pulled pork, brisket, and great fries.
Awesome place. Good food. BYOB.
Finally found some great bbq close to home. Have had BBQ all over the country and this ranks up there with the brisket in Texas.

So happy to see BBQ this close to home...I can smell them smoking from my house!  Very good food, many choices from sides to sauce.  Fun staff.  Beware the pulled pork burger, it's a gut buster full burger with a full helping of Pulled pork on top!  Ask for extra of your favorite sauce, killer corn bread, too!
First time enjoying his BBQ - authentic, not too sweet, not too spicy, complex and flavorful rub under a soothing and harmonious smoke.  Perfect!
great neighborhood feel staff is always great and food is excellent been there many times and love it
